liveLayoutDetails.notes: OB: OB on the left, right and behind the basket. ISLAND GREEN: Any throw from the Tee must come to rest on the Island Green to be able to mark on the Island Green. Throws from the Tee that do not come to rest on the Island Green must proceed to the Dropzone with a penalty throw. All other throws use normal OB rules.

OB: OB on the left, right and behind the basket. Normal OB rules apply. RELIEF AREA: Concrete building on the fairway, marked with pink paint/rope. Players can take up to 1m relief from the line.

OB: OB on the left, right and around the basket. All throws from the Tee play as normal OB rules. All throws from the inbounds fairway must come to rest on the Island Green to be able to mark on the Island Green. Throws from the inbounds fairway that do not come to rest on the Island Green, must play from the previous lie or where the disc was last inbounds on the fairway. All throws from the Island Green play as normal OB rules. MANDATORY: Play from the left side. If a disc clearly enters into the restricted plane proceed to the Dropzone with a penalty throw.
